## Conversation
PR2 of the SDK-uptake stack (plan: .context/sdk-uptake-plan.md). User goal:
remove RemoteHTTPTraceServer in favor of the weave-server-sdk-backed binding
as default. PR1 (parent commit) rewrote the stainless binding at parity; this
commit flips the default and deletes the old implementation.

## Actions
- weave_init.init_weave_get_server: unconditional StainlessRemoteHTTPTraceServer
  (lazy import kept deliberately — weave_server_sdk model definitions are a
  measurable import cost and import weave cold-start is a known hotspot).
- settings.py: removed use_stainless_server field + UserSettings entry +
  should_use_stainless_server(); api.py docstring entry removed.
- Deleted weave/trace_server_bindings/remote_http_trace_server.py and
  tests/trace_server_bindings/test_http_behavior_remote.py (its
  calls_complete/eager coverage was ported to the stainless flavor in PR1).
- tests/trace_server_bindings/conftest.py: single-impl server_class fixture;
  removed pytest_ignore_collect suffix filtering; SpyTransport moved here and
  shared by test files. test_http_behavior_stainless.py renamed to
  test_http_behavior.py. test_tags_aliases_routes.py rewritten via SpyTransport.
- tests/trace_server/conftest.py: removed --remote-http-trace-server flag and
  get_remote_http_trace_server_flag (no callers).
- tests/conftest.py: network_proxy_client now builds a TestClientTransport
  (httpx.BaseTransport routing into the FastAPI TestClient) injected via the
  binding's transport kwarg; processors patched in the stainless module;
  create_client legacy "http" branch switched.
- wal_sender.py switched to StainlessRemoteHTTPTraceServer (same Any cast).
- weave_client.py: endpoint probe now calls
  server.unretried_table_create_from_digests (new explicit single-attempt
  method on the binding) instead of poking _post_request_executor.__wrapped__.
- noxfile: stainless shard removed; test.yaml matrices drop "stainless"
  (added by PR1 — net effect across the stack: one bindings shard).

## Errors & Mistakes
- network_proxy tests failed first with ValueError "unknown url type:
  '/table/create'": I constructed the binding with trace_server_url="" so
  request URLs were relative, which breaks httpx cookie extraction
  (Cookies._CookieCompatRequest requires absolute URLs). Fix: base URL
  http://testserver; the injected transport routes by path and never dials.
- test_table_partitioning[True] then failed with 0 table_create_from_digests
  calls: the chunking probe silently degraded because the
  _post_request_executor internal no longer exists; check_endpoint_exists
  treats ANY exception (incl. AssertionError) as "endpoint missing". This
  failure mode is SILENT in prod (falls back to incremental upload) — worth
  remembering when touching probe code.

## Dead Ends
- Tried FastAPI TestClient directly as the SDK http_client (TestClient IS an
  httpx.Client) — but the binding builds its own client with hooks, and
  swapping the whole client loses the event hooks; the transport seam is the
  better-scoped injection point.

## Hints for Future Agents
- Pre-existing failures under `--trace-server=fake -p no:randomly` when run
  standalone (verified identical on parent commit): test_flask_server,
  test_evaluation_invalid_model_name_fixable/not_fixable (eval_imperative),
  test_from_obj_unwraps_nested_weave_object. NOT related to this stack.
- The binding's transport kwarg is the sanctioned test seam; tests should not
  monkeypatch weave.utils.http_requests for the remote binding anymore.
- check_endpoint_exists caches positive results in a global _ENDPOINT_CACHE
  keyed by "table_create_from_digests"; tests discard that key for
  determinism.

## Codebase Discoveries
- starlette's TestClient is an httpx.Client subclass; an httpx.BaseTransport
  adapter (TestClientTransport) cleanly bridges a sync httpx client into an
  ASGI app without anyio portals.
- get_trace_server_flag never returns "http"/"prod" (legacy dev-only
  branches in create_client; kept but switched to the new class).

